text: Only the otah was decent although $1.50 was on the ex side. The nasi lemak rice was nothing to shout about, the fish was so tiny. Chilli was spicy and sweet.
Nasi lemak just the usual, but otah is nice

Can’t say that we loved it, but it is a decent otah - would have loved that they keep it warm cos it was iced cold when we ate it and didn’t taste as good as it could have been.

Would not return since it’s not likely to be warm at the point of ordering.
The otah here has authentic colour (not bright red). A little spicy.
